<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-346] [PATCH] disable coord for generated BooleanQueries</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-346</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that disables Similiarty.coord() in the scoring of most&lt;br/&gt;
automatically generated boolean queries.  The coord() score factor is&lt;br/&gt;
appropriate when clauses are independently specified by a user, but is usually&lt;br/&gt;
not appropriate when clauses are generated automatically, e.g., by a fuzzy,&lt;br/&gt;
wildcard or range query.  Matches on such automatically generated queries are&lt;br/&gt;
currently penalized for not matching all terms.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: Linux&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: PC&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
